<b>The Anka-Team proudly presents Pisi Linux 1.0</b><br />
Pisi Linux is a 'rolling-release' GNU/Linux operating system.<br />It was created as a successor to the PiSi-based Pardus Linux, after it was declared End Of Life in 2012.<p></p>Pisi Linux contains several unique technologies:<br />
<b>COMAR</b> (COnfigurationMAnageR), configures and integrates installed software.<br />
<b>MUDUR</b>, designed to streamline the boot process. <br />
<b>PISI</b> (Packages Installed Successfully, as Intended), The packaging system developed for Pardus Linux.<br />
<b>YALI</b> (Yet Another Linux Installer), the custom installer. <br />
<b>KAPTAN</b>, a ‘desktop greeter’- automatically started post-install to assist with desktop preferences.<br />
<b>PANDA</b>, a video-driver manager (created by the Anka-Team).<br />

<br /><b>Release Highlights</b><br />
Linux Kernel: 3.12.8<br />
KDE: 4.11.5<br />
Mate: 1.6.2<br />
Mozilla Firefox: 26.0<br />
LibreOffice: 4.1.3.2<br />
GIMP: 2.8.10<br />
Calligra Suite: 2.7.5<br />
Clementine: 1.2.1<br />
Qt: 4.8.5<br />
glibc: 2.18<br />
binutils: 2.32.2<br />
coreutils: 8.21<br />

<br /><b>System Requirements</b>
<br />64-bit processor<br />
At least 2 GB memory and 12 GB disk space<br />
It is recomended to create swap space for Pisi Linux (can be done during installation)<br /><br />

<b>Multimedia</b><br />
Pisi Linux currently exists only in 64bit form. However, 32bit packages are included for applications such as<br /> Skype and Steam. Codecs for playing audio and video files are also included.<br /><br />

<b>Anything else ?</b><br />
There are over 6000 packages in our repositories, with more added all the time.<br />
Pisi Linux is translated to 14 languages: Turkish, English, Dutch, German, Russian, Spanish, French, Hungarian,<br /> Italian, Croatian, Swedish, Ukrainian, Polish and Portuguese (Brazil). Translation to other languages is on-going.<br /><br />
Turkish/English: Anka/Phoenix - Pisi/Kitty - Kaptan/Captain<br />
We hope you enjoy using Pisi Linux. Thank you.
